        <h2 class="section-heading" align="left">State channels</h2>
        <p>
        State channels are a protocols for secure transactions between a number of counterparties who do not wish to trust each other or an intermediary.
        </p>
        <p>
        They leverage a blockchain for security, but mostly bypass the usual high costs and high latency. 
        <p>
        At magmo we use a simple-but-powerful approach to develop new state channel protocols and software that are easy to use and understand.
        </p>
